President Biden and Prime Minister Modi held a meeting to discuss technology cooperation between India and the United States. They emphasized the importance of innovation and collaboration in tackling global challenges such as climate change, poverty, and healthcare. Both leaders expressed their commitment to expanding the partnership into new fields, including biotechnology and quantum technology. They also highlighted the need to address obstacles and build trust in emerging technologies. The CEOs present at the meeting were encouraged to provide input on the challenges they face and help shape the future of technological cooperation between the two countries. The meeting concluded with gratitude for the CEOs' participation and a focus on building a better future together.